The paper focuses on developing a novel approach for detecting large-variance code clones, which is a problem related to software engineering (cs.SE). The approach involves borrowing and changing the approach of sequencing alignment in bioinformatics, which suggests a possible connection to programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions bug detection and software analysis, which are topics related to computer security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG), respectively. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed approach on both synthetic and real datasets, which suggests a possible connection to software development (cs.SD).
